news.title: Panchshil Realty to invest Rs 1,000 crore to develop IT Park in Indore
news.para: The Pune headquartered realty firm has delivered more than 32 million sq ft of IT Park in Pune which has generated more than 6 lakh jobs.

news.title: Telangana HC restrains GHMC, revenue officials from interfering with Banjara Hills property
news.para: The direction was given while hearing a writ petition filed by Buddi Prakash Toshniwal and others, who claimed ownership of the 600 square yard property.

news.title: ED raids Ansal API offices in Delhi, Noida, and Ghaziabad over Rs 600 crore fraud
news.para: A six-member ED team, accompanied by security personnel, scrutinised electronic records, hard drives, financial documents, and bank accounts at the company's Lucknow office.

news.title: Chennai: GCC mandates builders to curb construction dust or face penalty
news.para: At least 6,150 metric tonnes of solid waste is generated daily in the city. Additionally, about 800 metric tonnes of construction and demolition (C&D) waste are generated every day.

news.title: Builder dupes over 32 tenants in Bengaluru by leasing already sold flats
news.para: In January 2024, a man named Sai Prashant visited Padma and claimed ownership of the same flats, presenting registered sale deeds dated September 13, 2021.

news.title: Schindler posts 2.5% rise in revenue in Q1 2025
news.para: The Americas account for 29% of Schindler's group revenue, with over 95% of the raw materials and components the company uses in products sold in the U.S. sourced locally, analysts at Jefferies said.

news.title: Vulcan Materials' revenues rises 5.8% to $1.64 billion in Q1 2025
news.para: These supplies are part of Vulcan's construction aggregates business, its largest. The segment's gross profit rose 18% in the quarter, while margins expanded 320 basis points to 26.7%.

news.title: Home prices in UK fall 0.6% in April 2025
news.para: House prices were 3.4% higher than a year ago, below a 3.9% rise in March and lagging a consensus for a 4.1% annual increase.

news.title: Germany eases property regulations as real estate concerns subside
news.para: BaFin, the German financial regulator, said on Wednesday that it would trim to 1% from 2% the amount it requires banks to hold as capital for residential mortgage loans.

news.title: Kalyan Dombivli civic body demolishes 167 illegal constructions in Baneli area
news.para: This action was taken amid heavy security and faced opposition from locals in the Baneli area of Titwala, which falls under the jurisdiction of KDMC.

news.title: Lawyer Arun Kathpalia buys bungalow at Delhi’s Golf Links for Rs 69 crore
news.para: Golf Links and Sunder Nagar have emerged as particular favourites for lawyers due to their proximity to the high court and the Supreme Court.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income up 13% in Q4 FY25
news.para: The board considered and approved the distribution of ₹6.44 per unit aggregating to ₹3,923.14 million for the quarter ended March 31, 2025.

news.title: Bihar: Saran district collects Rs 200 crore revenue through land registration
news.para: The district collected over Rs 200 crore revenue this fiscal. A district administration official said the district received Rs 210.98 crore in 2024-25, which was Rs 37 crore more than revenue collected last fiscal.

news.title: Kanpur civic body removes over 500 illegal constructions
news.para: The mayor and the municipal commissioner Sudhir Kumar are taking effective action through a joint encroachment campaign to provide relief to the people of the city from problems of water logging and jam.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body mulls higher property tax to deter garbage dumping
news.para: Although some offenders settle their fines when caught, others refuse payment. To resolve this issue, GHMC plans to incorporate these unsettled penalties into property tax collections.

news.title: Chandigarh: 300 properties removed from the "resumed" list
news.para: Nishant Kumar Yadav, deputy commissioner and estate officer, said, "There were 600 properties marked as resumed in the estate office online records.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body plans to launch awareness drive on CCs & OCs of housing projects
news.para: The campaign comes in response to numerous complaints by homebuyers facing difficulties in obtaining essential services due to the absence of the mandatory certificates.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT sends proposal to NMC to take over 185 developed layouts
news.para: While developing the layouts, the NIT collected development charges from the owners and developed the layouts.

news.title: Supreme Universal sells duplex apartment for ₹174 crore in Mumbai
news.para: The two-floor sea-facing apartment has been purchased by Sarvesh Singh, executive director of Alkem Laboratories.
